devdoc.custom:experimental: This is an experimental contract/library. Use at your own risk.

checkUpkeep(address).details: Function which checks if any of the registered core contracts require upkeep

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pauseContract(address).details: Pauses a core contract from upkeep services

performUpkeep(address,address).details: Calls deposit function in a core contract. Should be used by keepers.

params._depositToken: Address of the token to be deposited

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unPauseContract(address).details: Unpauses a core contract from upkeep services

params._contract: Address of the core contract Unpausing and adding a contract are equivalent actions in our case
